DefaultDialogue: Ah, a visitor! I can tell by your starry-eyed demeanor that this is the first time you have ever set eyes on a city such as ours! \n\nFor a small fee, I can arrange for a guide to give you the grand tour. Simply say the word!

Making yourself at home, I trust? You must get so tired, running about all over. \n\nThe inn has only the highest quality beds. You will find your rest more than adequate. I will personally guarantee it!
I have it on good authority that you are becoming a regular around here. \n\nNot causing any trouble, I hope? No, of course not. Not an upstanding citizen such as yourself.
Your pockets sound entirely too heavy. I can recommend some choice venues to leave some of it for our communal coffers. \n\nA settlement this grand does not pay for itself!
You return! I think you will be delighted to learn that our little problem with the Corrupted appears to have taken care of itself. \n\nAll's well that ends well.
A fine day, is it not? The autumnal splendor of Everfall is always on full display. \n\nStay a while, enjoy the scenery, and be sure to buy a drink at the tavern!
I see you have my flute! Do you mean to awe me with a song? \n\nI will always make time for pleasant music. It gives me great joy. Do proceed.
My, my, my! \n\nTo whom do I owe this wonderous experience?
I have seen you puttering about town before, and quite busily at that! Seeking rumors and ghosts and all manner of snooping. \n\nJust what have you been up to, hm? A magistrate has a right to know.
Where has Riker gotten off to? The man best not be in the belly of some beast. \n\nHe gets so cranky when he dies.
You've done us a great turn, getting more sustenance into the settlement. The gap between the rich and the poor grows steady here in Everfall. \n\nAs for the rich, though, the noble families…
The nobles are loving those fur coats! Next thing you know, they'll be asking about my fancy trousers. \n\nWho doesn't want to strike as fine a figure as Huntsman Lee?
What's that you're holding? \n\nI could use a good strong brew before me next hunt.
If you've come by any quality furs, do know that I pay handsomely for the right pelts. \n\nOr did you come seeking fashion advice?
I am really not sure why they chose me for this post. None of the guards listen to me, really. \n\nCaptain Dubois seems to be the only one who can command their attention!

Every time you cross that threshold, I cringe a little. There is a loose floorboard just to the left of the entry, and in my mind's eye, I see you taking a great tumble. \n\nOh no, that sounded like a threat! I promise it was not!
I burned my hand cooking breakfast this morning… it feels like an omen. \n\nThere isn't anything I should know about, is there? Maybe Franc has heard something…
I am going to need to ask a priest to consecrate this place after you brought that language in here. \n\nNo, no, don't say anything else. Let's just forget this ever happened.
At the risk of inviting ill luck, I must tell you that your fears were unfounded. \n\nWe've received word the Corruption is actually receding from the northern farms. One less thing to worry about!
Have you come to report a crime? \n\nI believe my guard captain, Franc, is better suited to handle the situation.
Was that the lilting of a flute I heard? Yes, I do have a sharp ear. \n\nIf your work is of such quality, I know several individuals who would be delighted to learn your name. Play for me?
Yes. Yes, this is exactly what this town needs. I shall ensure your name is spoken far and wide. \n\nWhen you earn yourself a patron, do remember who helped grow your career!
Well that’s a serious face if I've ever seen one. \n\nIs anything amiss? Do I need to summon a guard?
I have not seen your face around Everfall before. \n\nTread carefully, adventurer. Danger lurks outside of the settlement.
My soul feels less heavy, less prone to the madness of being Lost. \n\nThank you again for all you've done for Audrey and me.
You smell of perfume. Have you been to see Huntsman Lee? What does he want now?
I have not seen your face around Everfall before. \n\nTread carefully, adventurer. Danger lurks outside of the settlement.
I have not seen your face around Everfall before. \n\nTread carefully, adventurer. Danger lurks outside of the settlement.
I assume you informed the Captain of the Guard about the Corruption, and he did nothing? \n\nTypical. Everfall is blind to anything that doesn't glitter.
I assume you informed the Captain of the Guard about the Corruption, and he did nothing? \n\nTypical. Everfall is blind to anything that doesn't glitter.
If you're still keen on destroying Corruption, go back to the settlement and update Huntsman Lee with our progress. \n\nHe will want to know what we've done.
These foul Corrupted will suffer as I have.\n\nI'm sure they can still feel pain. I'm sure they can howl with anguish.
These foul Corrupted will suffer as I have.\n\nI'm sure they can still feel pain. I'm sure they can howl with anguish.
That locket reminds me of happier days.\n\nDays when we would go to Meadowlake Fishery to gather her favorite flowers, and watch the sun set across the water...
You have been a balm to my weary heart, {playerName}, but I… I need some time alone. \n\nLee must be worried sick by now. You can go put his mind at ease.
You look strong, friend. You should consider joining the Marauders.\n\nWe will put that strength to use.
I salute you, fellow Marauder. \n\nWe will never give up the fight, and in the end, we will emerge victorious.
I salute you, fellow Marauder. \n\nWe will never give up the fight, and in the end, we will emerge victorious.
I’m with the Syndicate, the true inheritors of the Ancients' legacy. \n\nWe are committed to harnessing the power of Azoth and ushering in a new and never-ending age of enlightenment for all.
I greet you in reverence, fellow pursuer of knowledge.
I greet you in reverence, fellow pursuer of knowledge.
We are the Covenant. We are driven to protect this place, defend the helpless, and administer justice. \n\n I serve as the Adjudicator for this settlement.
The light of the Covenant shines within you.
The light of the Covenant shines within you.
Oh hello there! You are most welcome to the Everfall tavern. \n\nSit down, imbibe, take a moment to enjoy life.
I've been toying with the idea of renaming my bar. Perhaps after that fortuitous bottle of Commandaria. \n\nOr maybe after you, {playerName}? How'd you like your name on a pretty painted sign?
What's all this, now? A bottle of wine? \n\nI didn't order this. It's a generous gift, but what's all this about?
A bard? Good. I could use someone to liven up the place a bit. \n\nTake your place by the fire, love.
A shame the usual crowd wasn't here to enjoy that, but I'll be singing your praises. \n\nI hope you can come back and play another night.
I can see that you're new to Aeternum. Strong arms, though--clearly a warrior. \n\nI'm sure you have plenty of… whatever it is you do. Good day!
Since you are clearly no ordinary muscle for hire, would you be interested in collaborating with me? \n\nThink about the possibilities. Your brawn, my brain, and a host of mysteries to solve.

Let us assume that the Ancients were not wasteful in what they built. \n\nHere's a tentative hypothesis: the towers only function when they are activated. The guardians merely deter intruders from tampering with them.
At the very least, lighting up the towers proves they have some active function. \n\nThey are more than mere monuments to the Ancients' power, and all my efforts haven't been a waste of time.
It wasn't all in vain. With a working armillary sphere, I can start making sense of the Ancients' view of the heavens. \n\nOr trying to, at any rate. It may take me several more lifetimes.
Towers in the earth, constellations above, a universe of endless void… \n\nSomething is missing... Some piece that I've carelessly overlooked. What is it?
Perhaps it's time to try a different approach. Gather information from a different source. \n\nWhat have you been doing with the Ancient guardians who try to attack you?
Now, the moment of truth, when all my theories are put to the test. \n\nTell me, have you ever heard of an armillary sphere?
You've done so much for me and my research, friend. \n\nYou remind me of one of my former colleagues, Simon Grey. We had a bit of a rivalry, as you might imagine.

Based on the Foreman's Ledger you recovered, it's clear that the Amrine Excavation delved into an underground network of ruins that actually led to the Shattered Obelisk!\n\nI knew there was more to that place!
Together, we have uncovered more insights into the Ancients than anyone else in Aeternum history.\n\nHear that, Simon Grey? Oh sorry, that's disrespectful, isn't it? But who cares? I don't!
Welcome to 'The Autumn Rest'! Always a colorful place to be.\n\nYou here to check in? Be my guest… literally!
Hi there! I'm Master Fisher Ruby! Are you new to fishing?
Hi there! I'm Master Fisher Ruby! Are you new to fishing?
I'm so proud of you out there fishing.
Winter Convergence is upon us. You lack the strength of heart to be able to assist me, but if you come back stronger, I have a request for you.

Once again we see the two sides of winter converging: the warmth of kinship and the bitter cold of ice.\n\nImagine Aeternum, covered in rime and frost in every corner… This could be our fate in the Forever Winter.
Yeti use winter magic to spread ice and snow. This ice comes alive, steals presents from humans.\n\nWithout joy, how will we fight off Forever Winter?
Many ways to get to Aeternum, but no way out.\n\nAt least here we have Gleamite Crystals. They radiate warmth without burning, and are the bane of the Winter Warrior.
Each time Warrior is brought down he is weaker.\n\nThe weaker the Warrior is, the better for Aeternum. This I know from my Mirgos memories, my human memories you helped bring back.
Your triumph over Winter Warrior keeps back the fate of Forever Winter.\n\nSave presents, mine Gleamite Crystals, and challenge Warrior for the sake of warmth, light, and all that is good.
Did you see my cart? The wilds of Aeternum have never been safe, but the roads?\n\nNever seen anything like this before today! Vicious boars came out of nowhere - ate all my truffles!
Oh, I think we'll be seeing more of each other down the road a piece.\n\nYes, indeed. Always down the road a piece.

You look like a smart individual. I bet you'd love to make yourself rich, like me. \n\nI tell you, corner the market on iron. You can't go wrong, everyone needs iron! It's just like gold, only more useful in the long run.

Here for more tips? I knew you’d be back. \n\nLook. Forget iron, orichalcum is where it’s at! Buy now, sell high later, you won't regret it! It's how you can save up for three houses. I should know, it's how I saved up for mine!
One day, my fine friend, one day you shall be strong enough to participate in a glorious spectacle!\n\nKeep training, and return to me when you have a want to prove yourself in combat with allies.
Step right up, step right up, for a showdown you will never forget! Two teams enter, and after a clash of skill and brutality a team emerges victorious! Are you courageous enough to brave… the Arena?
There's my champion! Up for another bout? You can access the Arena through your map, don't forget!
I’ll dredge up a few more challengers…
Have you also come to laugh at me? \n\nIt was an accident, I swear…
I've gone and spoiled everything, absolutely everything with my clumsiness. \n\nHave you also come to laugh at me?
This vase is even grander than the one I broke. Priceless, even. \n\nAnd those fascinating symbols must mean something. They can't merely be decorative…
Just look at them, shoving tentpoles into the ground and tearing up the earth! \n\nHave they no respect for this ancient place?
Hello again, friend. Imagine meeting you here. \n\nI found some antiquarians to help me assess the vase we found, and… well... they convinced me to join them. I'm working on some field studies here.

Without your aid, I never would've had the courage to pursue my true passion. \n\nPerhaps with the passage of time, my family will finally understand what they have overlooked all these years. I am my own person.
Unless you intend to risk life and limb for the sake of sport, I suggest you keep an eye out for bears. \n\nThey wander this stretch of forest.
You, there! Ever been mauled? \n\nDeath escapes us on this island, so why not go up against a bear? Can you prove yourself tough enough to withstand the razor sharp teeth and claws of a killer?
The second best part of being mauled, right after the thrill, is the bragging rights! You know who this will really impress? Huntsman Lee. \n\nOdnell's an odd man but he appreciates a lurid story.
There you are, my bear-hunting friend! \n\nUp for another round?
Polly, my sweet Polly. I've failed you for the last time. \n\nAll I wanted was to see you smile again, but I can barely muster a smile for myself.
Leave me be. What's the point in dragging myself down the road? \n\nIt'll be the same no matter what I do. Thieves, pirates, and murderers without a scrap of mercy for a poor soul.
Since you seem to have a shred of kindness, I thought maybe… you could find my missing wine shipment? \n\nIt was stolen weeks ago. Probably gone or drunk now, but I thought I'd ask.
I remember a face, and a laugh crueler than the Devil's. Admiral Arias, at the Arias Encampment. \n\nHe was the first to come after me on the road. I hear he's Lost now, but it's a cold comfort.
I dare not risk so valuable a vintage. If I tried to carry it, with my luck? Something terrible would happen. \n\nCan you bring this priceless treasure to Polly? By itself, it'll erase all her debts!
Polly's saved, my wares are restored, and Admiral Arias hasn't been scouring the roads of late. \n\nAll of this may seem a small kindness to you, friend. But to me, it meant everything.
You're looking a bit peaky, traveler. \n\nWhether it's a stiff leg, sore head, or the simple ennui of life, Anwir Hughes has an elixir for you!

Twenty coin, only twenty coin for a bottle of Anwir's Elixir. Thirty-five for two, even cheaper for repeat customers. \n\nYou, there! How would you like to feel younger, stronger, and better looking today?
Ahh, the irreplaceable smell of nature. It always puts pep in my step and makes me feel young again. \n\nIf I could find a way to bottle that scent, I'd make a fortune!
My perceptive friend, fancy meeting you again. \n\nDo you remember my Ancient Miracle Elixir?
Finally, we reach my favorite part. Distributing free samples to needy townsfolk. \n\nOnce they've had a taste, they'll be throwing coin at me for more! Do let me know how it goes.
What next? Anwir's Ancient Miracle Elixir is all very well and good, but customers crave novelty. \n\nCrystals and gemstones, perhaps? Everybody loves a big, sparkling rock.
I am afraid I have little time for casual conversation, stranger. \n\nMy proprietor keeps my hands busy at all times.
Hmm, hmm hmm… No, more lilting. Perhaps with a key change. No, let it breathe. \n\nOh! You caught me unawares. How may I be of assistance?
I must ask your patience while I compose. \n\nMy process can be a lengthy one, and I wish to do so in solitude.

Ah! There you are. My magnum opus is complete! I shall call it… Winds of Autumn! \n\nNow I must ensure it is heard far and wide. Without popular excitement, I will never gain the favor of a suitable patron.
I hope we have done enough to spread my fame. Without that reputation, I fear I will never earn a proper patron. \n\nMy duty to my Mistress is wearing me thin.

This is terrible, my friend. I heard that my Mistress was interested in backing my pen name and revealed to her that it was me. I had expected… \n\nAt any rate… my pay has been docked, and I am not to speak of it again.
Saira winked at me as I walked past. She knows something, and she seems very smug about it. \n\nI confess, I am having difficulty containing my eagerness.
Look at this… the embossed wax seal, the heft of the paper… even the ink is gilt in gold. Every detail screams affluence, and yet it is hardly overt. \n\nThis letter summons me to Lord Shen's side.
Any packages meant for the household can be given to me. \n\nWhat's this? Anwir's Ancient Miracle Elixir? What a bizarre name.
If you are looking for my proprietors, I am afraid they are not taking appointments today. \n\nUnless there is something else I can assist you with?

I cannot bear the thought of facing Lady Sacco myself. Lord Shen reassured me that there would be no need. \n\nWhat if she chooses not to part with me? Will she truly stoop to quashing my life's ambition?

Thank you, my dear friend. Our mutual efforts have succeeded. I stand poised on the precipice of greatness, with my patron at my back. \n\nRest assured, I will not forget your part in this. I shall see your name praised.
You must be new to town. I would remember a face like yours. \n\nIf you come across any interesting gossip, do be sure to let me know. I might have a favor to offer in exchange.
I heard you thrumming and twanging from over here. I did not know you could play. \n\nThat skill may very well come in handy in this town.
My, my. Whoever is this "Composer Marsyas?" I would put good money on that being a pen name. \n\nNow, I must know someone who's been dabbling in music of late…?
You best believe I am going to dangle that little favor over Atticus for a good while yet. \n\n Thank you for your part in this, it really made my day.
Now that Atticus is a member of our household, I get to hold my favor over him all I want. Delightful. I love watching him squirm. \n\nAnd I suppose I should thank you, for the amusement of it all.
You got that look on your face. You know the one. Preparing to ask for something that's above your station, hm? \n\nWell, get on with it.
Do you have the items I requested? \n\nHand them over, and I'll evaluate how you've done.
Try not to look so lost, lamb. It attracts pickpockets. \n\nNo, don't go clutching your valuables either. That's even worse.
Do I know you? Hmph. \n\nWhatever your business, you should speak to my manservant, Atticus. I am terribly busy, you see.
Constable Maecia alerted me to a new force in the music world. One Composer Marsyas, I am told.\n\nI am determined to learn more. Perhaps their work may be auspicious enough to earn my backing.
Composer Marsyas indeed. Oh, I have never been more affronted in my LIFE! \n\nYou tell that deceitful manservant that he is lucky to remain in my employ!
We are no longer on speaking terms. \n\nBegone.
I knew it! It was you who spread those ridiculous rumors. \n\nYou filled my darling Atticus' head with flights of fancy, and now look! He seeks to exit my employ!
Are you intentionally trying to waste my time? \n\nI told you! I will not part with my dear Atticus. Nothing from Lord Shen could possibly change my mind!

How curious. You approach unannounced and unaccompanied. Perhaps you do not understand basic etiquette. \n\nIgnorance deserves patience, but I caution you against such impropriety in the future. I bid you farewell.
Again, you approach without prior arrangement. \n\nI am beginning to view this as impertinence, stranger.

Your name has been mentioned, although I have already forgotten it. As you are known to my associates, I shall not call for a guard. \n\nLeave me. I will summon you when I wish to speak again. I hope we understand one another.
You have done well to bring this composer to my attention. \n\nHe will represent my house well, and I shall take pride in being his patron.

Marsyas, or should I say Atticus, has told me a great deal about you. It seems I have you to thank for this auspicious meeting. \n\nI have decided to grant Atticus my esteemed patronage, but it comes with a condition.
Well? What is her price? \n\nI have deep pockets, after all, but I am sure she will not part with him easily.
The writing on this fragment of paper is barely legible and covered in suspicious dark stains.
By picking up the paper and holding it up to the light, you can see a few lines of text. \n\n"Superiora de inferioribus, inferiora de superioribus."
The paper fragment is already crumbling to pieces. \n\nSoon, there will be nothing left of it.
Riker--Fallowhill Farm should have what we're looking for. Food for the masses, not just the elite. \n\nBe wary of the wolves and you should be just fine. -Lee
Riker--Fallowhill Farm should have what we're looking for. Food for the masses, not just the elite. \n\nBe wary of the wolves and you should be just fine. -Lee
Riker--Fallowhill Farm should have what we're looking for. Food for the masses, not just the elite. \n\nBe wary of the wolves and you should be just fine. -Lee
A set of Ancient scrolls with indecipherable glyphs lies before you.
A set of Ancient scrolls with indecipherable glyphs lies before you. \n\nPerhaps an inquiring mind would be curious to their value?
I do wonder if I should go back to the family manor. Send a note? \n\nBut if they were truly worried about me, surely they would not have exiled me over a broken vase!
Audrey, every day that passes without you, I feel myself growing more hollow.\n\nI only hope I can remember you should I succumb to that despair.
Before you lies a locket with the initials 'TP+AK' expertly carved into it.
You've retrieved the locket that once lay here for Tekla Petrowski.
What is it? \n\nThere is no rest for those who seek the universe's mysteries.

Call down the starlight. Hah, all that for a silly parlor trick! \n\nDespite my disappointment, this recipe was a valuable find. A sharp reminder that the mysterious infinite laughs at our puny efforts.

The obelisks left behind by the Ancients seem to have multiple functions: drawing power, and using that power for some defensive purpose.  \n\nI have recorded two particular towers of interest, Orion and Draco. -WH

The obelisks left behind by the Ancients seem to have multiple functions: drawing power, and using that power for some defensive purpose. \n\nI have recorded two particular towers of interest, Orion and Draco. -WH
You have successfully reunited William Heron with his lost field notes.
Welcome to Everfall, the prosperous beating heart of Aeternum. \n\nI know how it sounds, please don't scoff. The words are not mine, I'm just paid to say them.
Something to report? I'm only allowed to deal with minor public disturbances. \n\nFor any mercantile disputes, you'll have to plead your case with one of the noble families.
Mired in mud, the owner of this cart is nowhere to be seen.\n\nNothing remains of their cargo save some dusty paper and scraps of stone.
Mired in mud, the owner of this cart is nowhere to be seen.\n\nNothing remains of their cargo save some dusty paper and scraps of stone.
